            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1717777699843-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1717777699843-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pepper has started to soften, add your <strong>ground cumin</strong> and <strong>chipotle paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add your <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>to the pan with the <strong>drained black beans</strong> and your <strong>vegetable stock</strong> <strong>mix</strong></p><p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until the sauce has thickened</p>",
